## Coding style
- Frontend: Keep HTML accessible; prefer Bootstrap utilities over custom CSS where feasible.
- Frontend: Organize scripts with small, reusable functions; avoid global state.
- Backend: Use async/await for all I/O operations (database, file access).
- Backend: Follow SOLID principles, keep controllers/endpoints thin, business logic in services.
- Backend: Use proper error handling with try-catch and return appropriate HTTP status codes.
- No heavy formatting frameworks; keep Prettier defaults unless the user provides a config.

